CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Chapeaux!  That's French for hat...and that seems to be the main item here, as Misses Catherine Muldrow and Doris Clark pause to smile pretty for the lensman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Catherine Muldrow and Doris Clark (Moody) wearing gloves, coats, and hats with netting, standing outside of Falk School, University of Pittsburgh, Oakland
